{
	"title": "Stolen Memories: Leveraging Model Memorization for Calibrated White-Box Membership Inference",
	"authors": [
		"Klas Leino",
		"Matt Fredrikson"
	],
	"conference": "USENIX",
	"year": "2020",
	"date": "2020/10/01",
	"tldr": "This work demonstrates how a model's idiosyncratic use of features can leak information about its training data to an attacker with access to the model's parameters&mdash;even when the model's black-box behavior appears to generalize well. We use our analysis to derive a white-box *membership inference* attack that this attack outperforms prior black-box methods.",
	"keywords": [
		"ML Security",
		"Data Privacy"
	],
	"links": [
